29/06/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- US Ambassador to Tirana Marcie B. Ries reiterated on Tuesday (28 June) that the 3 July parliamentary elections are key to the country's bid to join Euro-Atlantic structures. Ries urged authorities to ensure full compliance with international standards. 
Separately Tuesday, Albanian President Alfred Moisiu again asked all parties and independent candidates to respect the political Code of Conduct. He also urged the army, police and the judiciary to act independently, transparently and impartially during the election process. (Albanian News - 29/06/05; Albanian President Web site - 28/06/05)
